1. Open Postman and create a collection. Name it "EECS 4413 Auction UC7".

2. Make a new request and name it "CSRF Token".

3. Change the method to "GET" and type: "http://localhost:8000/auth/csrf/" onto the URL bar.

4. Click Send. You should receive a 200 OK on the console.

5. Click on Cookies, then click "csrftoken". Copy and paste the value of "csrftoken".

NOTE: At any point, the system will say that the CSRF Token has expired. Just redo Step 5 for any request.

6. Make a new request and name it "Sign-Up".

7. Change the method to "POST" and type: "http://localhost:8000/auth/signup/ onto the URL bar.

8. Go to the Headers tab.

9. Make two key-value pairs: The first one "Content-Type" with "aaplication/json", the second one "X-CSRFToken" with your pasted token under the Value column.

10. Go to the Body tab.

11. Put "raw" under the first drop down menu and "JSON" in the second.

12. In the JSON body, make an account with username, email, password, password2, first_name, last_name, street_name, street_number, city, country, postal_code.

13. Click Send. You should have received 201 Created.

14. Make a new request and name it "Create New Item".

15. Change the method to "POST" and type: "http://localhost:8000/items/create/" onto the URL bar.

16. Repeat Step 8-11.

17. In the JSON body, make an item with name, description, current_price, starting_price, auction_type: "FORWARD", end_time: "2025-12-31T23:59:00Z"

18. Click Send. You should received 201 Created along with the information you created for the item in addition to the seller. This should create an item with index 1.

19. Make a new request and name it "Auction Ended Item 1".

20. Change the method to "GET" and type: "http://localhost:8000/1/ended/" onto the URL bar.

21. Repeat Step 8-11.

22. In the JSON body, type in the username and password when you made your account.

23. Click Send. You should have received a 400 Bad Request with the message: "Auction still ongoing".

24. If you want to create an item that has its auction ended, repeat step 14-18, but at step 17, replace the end_time with "2024-12-31T23:59:00Z". This is a date that has past.

25. If you want to see the item you created in the previous that has its auction ended, repeat step 19-22, but at step 20, type: "http://localhost:8000/2/ended/" onto the URL bar. This is your second item created.

26. Click Send. You should have received a 200 OK with '"status": "no_bids", "message": "Auction ended with no bids."'.
